{
    "directions": [
        "In a food processor, pur\u00e9e mango, adding 1 tbsp water, if necessary, to achieve a puddinglike consistency. Add spices; blend thoroughly. Add sugar to taste. Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours. When ready to serve, cut watermelon in half. Using a melon baller, scoop out about 2 cups of balls. Pour pur\u00e9e into 4 shallow bowls and arrange melon balls on top. Garnish with mint sprigs."
    ],
    "ingredients": [
        "2 1/2 cups diced fresh mango",
        "1/2 teaspoon ground nutmeg",
        "1/2 teaspoon cinnamon",
        "1/2 teaspoon ground ginger",
        "Confectioners' sugar",
        "1 small watermelon (preferably seedless)",
        "Mint sprigs, for garnish"
    ],
